==English==

===Pronunciation===
*(''RP''): {{AHD|skô}}, {{IPA|/skɔː/}}, {{SAMPA|/skO:/}}
*(''US''): {{AHD|skôr}}, {{IPA|/skoʊr/}}, {{IPA|/skɔːr/}}, {{SAMPA|/skO:r/}}
*Rhymes: [[rhymes:English:-ɔː(r)|-ɔː(r)]]

===Etymology===
*{{OE.}} ''[[scora]]'': a notch, hence a [[tally]].
*(For 'twenty'): The mark on a tally made by drovers for every twenty beasts passing through a [[tollgate]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The total number of [[point]]s earned by a [[participant]] in a [[game]].
# [[Twenty]] ([[number]]).
#: ''Some words have scores of meanings.''
#: ''Four score and seven years ago...''
# {{music}} A book or set of pages showing all the parts for a [[musical]] [[composition]].
#{{cricket}} a presentation of how many [[run]]s a side has scored, and how many [[wicket]]s have been lost
#: ''England had a score of 107 for 5 at lunch.''
#{{cricket}} the number of runs scored by a [[batsman]], or by a side, in either an [[innings]] or a [[match]]

